Class PingStage

java.lang.Object

          org.jscsi.target.connection.stage.fullfeature.PingStage

public class PingStage
extends TargetFullFeatureStage

A stage for processing NOP-Out PDUs, which are used by the initiator for pinging the target, making sure that the connection is still up.

The execute(ProtocolDataUnit) method will process these ping messages and send a NOP-In PDU as ping echo, containing a copy of the NOP-Out PDU's data segment.

If either the NOP-OUT PDU's initiator or target transfer tag equals the reserved value of 0xffffffff, then no reply will be sent, since the PDU is only supposed to acknowledge a changed ExpCmdSN, or serve as an echo to a NOP-IN ping sent by the target.

Author:
Andreas Ergenzinger
